race.comment: ITSZARBABY (5) hit the frame two starts ago at Nowra but ran below par last time over 1200m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Finds a nice race and can turn things around. BRUMMAGEN (2) has put together back-to-back placings, the latest when a long neck away in second over 800m at Gilgandra. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. LOUD (13) doesn't win out of turn but is knocking on the door. Gets the chance to take closer order from the inside alley and is worth including. TANGO ON (3) was a brave on-pace winner here two back to shed his maiden tag. Less effective last time at Nowra but is well placed back at this venue. Don't dismiss easily.
